This paper deals with the problem of Multi-agent Path Finding (MAPF), which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Robotics (cs.RO). The proposed algorithm involves prioritized planning, which is a common technique in Multi-agent Systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the use of graphs and cycles, which are topics in Data Structures (cs.DS). Finally, the evaluation of the algorithm through simulation involves control and optimization, which are relevant to Systems and Control (cs.SY).
